      </p>
      <p>
        There are some issues with using a linear line of best fit. As discussed
        in the hypothesis section, the domain of the line of best fit would be
        from 0 to the maximum concentration of sodium chloride in water. The
        maximum mass of sodium chloride dissolved in water at 25°C is 0.009 kg
        (Engineering Toolbox n.d). When extrapolated, the graph does not predict
        an unreasonable result for 0.009 kg of sodium chloride dissolved.
      </p>
